vxWorksVersion.name: vxWorksVersion
vxWorksVersion.description: The version of the underlying VxWorks operating system.

creationDate.name: creationDate
creationDate.description: The date and time the Access Point system code was initially compiled.

awcVxVersion.name: awcVxVersion
awcVxVersion.description: The version of the Access Point system code.

sysFlags.name: sysFlags
sysFlags.description: The VxWorks sysFlags system-configuration flags in use by the Access Point system. Not used by system code with awcVxVersion from 10.00 to 11.06.

languageCode.name: languageCode
languageCode.description: The language currently in use by the system. Max. string length is 128 octets.

awcDevID.name: awcDevID
awcDevID.description: The Aironet DDP protocol device ID of the system when using the full capabilities with which the system is licensed. Note that a system may be configured to use fewer capabilities that those for which it is licensed. For example, a Bridge may be configured for use as an Access Point.

awcDevIDtxt.name: awcDevIDtxt
awcDevIDtxt.description: Textual representation of awcDevID. Max. string length is 128 octets.

enableHTTP.name: enableHTTP
enableHTTP.description: If true, the Access Point's HTTP server can accept connections from other network devices. If false, the Access Point's HTTP server will only accept connections from the Access Point's console or indirectly over TELNET.

enableTelnet.name: enableTelnet
enableTelnet.description: If true, the Access Point's TELNET server can accept connections from other network devices. If false, all TELNET connections will be refused.

enableSNMP.name: enableSNMP
enableSNMP.description: If true, the Access Point's SNMP agent can accept connections from other network devices. If false, all SNMP connections will be refused. Note that this can only be set to false by an SNMP management station. If false, it can only be set to true by non-SNMP means.

enableDnsResolver.name: enableDnsResolver
enableDnsResolver.description: If true, the Access Point will attempt to resolve IP address references through all configured DNS servers and will attempt to perform reverse-lookup via all configured DNS servers when displaying IP addresses. If false, the Access Point will interpret and display only explicit numeric IP addresses.

enableSNTP.name: enableSNTP
enableSNTP.description: If true, the Access Point will attempt to periodically update its wall-clock time via a configured SNTP server. If false, the Access Point wall-clock time must be manually adjusted.

enableWDB.name: enableWDB
enableWDB.description: If true, the Access Point will enable use of the VxWorks WDB debugger upon its next reboot. If false, no WDB debugging services will be available after the next reboot. The value of enableWDB is applicable only to special diagnostic versions of the Access Point system code.

pingTxLen.name: pingTxLen
pingTxLen.description: The size in octets of ping packets transmitted by the Access Point. Default 64.

awcFirstBoot.name: awcFirstBoot
awcFirstBoot.description: If true, no user-specified configuration has been saved by the Access Point since either the system left Cisco manufacturing or since the user performed a Reset All System Factory Defaults operation. If false, a change in configuration has been saved by the user. Note that configurations specified solely via boot protocols such as DHCP or BOOTP are not considered user-specified for purposes of changing awcFirstBoot.

awcOemOUI.name: awcOemOUI
awcOemOUI.description: The IEEE Organizationally Unique Identifier of the reseller for which this system is branded.

awcOemName.name: awcOemName
awcOemName.description: The full name of the reseller for which this system is branded.

awcOemNameShort.name: awcOemNameShort
awcOemNameShort.description: An abbreviated name of the reseller for which this system is branded.

awcOemHomeURL.name: awcOemHomeURL
awcOemHomeURL.description: The URL of the corporate HTML home page of the reseller for which this system is branded.

enablePSPF.name: enablePSPF
enablePSPF.description: If true, Publicly-Secure Packet Forwarding mode is enabled (i.e. clients can not communicate with each other). If false, normal packet forwarding is used.

sysExceptionReboot.name: sysExceptionReboot
sysExceptionReboot.description: If true, all access violations or other general faults in any task will result in a reboot of the system. If false, such errors will not result in a reboot, and thus diagnostics can be performed on the system.

bootblockVersion.name: bootblockVersion
bootblockVersion.description: The version of the Access Point boot block (bootstrap loader) code.

motherboardRevision.name: motherboardRevision
motherboardRevision.description: Revision number of the Access Point system motherboard.

enableSTP.name: enableSTP
enableSTP.description: If true and the system is licensed with Bridge capabilities, the IEEE 802.1D Spanning Tree Protocol will be be used to control packet forwarding on all network interfaces. If false or the system is not licensed with Bridge capabilities, the system will use Access Point heuristics to control packet forwarding on all network interfaces.

enableRebootKey.name: enableRebootKey
enableRebootKey.description: If true, the VxWorks Monitor Trap keystroke is enabled from the console and from Telnet. By default, this is <control-X>. Entering this character initiates a warm-restart of the system. If false, the VxWorks Monitor Trap keystroke is disabled.

awcLocateUnit.name: awcLocateUnit
awcLocateUnit.description: If true, the unit will immediately begin flashing all three of its Status LEDs with an alternating pattern of amber and off. If false, the Status LEDs operate in their normal fashion.

bootconfigBootProtocol.name: bootconfigBootProtocol
bootconfigBootProtocol.description: The protocol to be used for automatic configuration at the time of system bootstrap/reboot. Options BOOTP, DHCP, or none.

bootconfigReadINI.name: bootconfigReadINI
bootconfigReadINI.description: If always, the system will attempt to read a .ini-formatted configuration file upon every reboot. If never, the system will not attempt to read a .ini file upon reboot, even if a boot protocol is in use and the boot server specifies a file to be read. If ifSpecified, the system will attempt to read a .ini file upon reboot if and only if a boot protocol is in use and the boot server explicitly specifies a file to be read. The system attempts several filenames in the process of retrieving a .ini file without error. In order, these filenames are based on the system's BOOTP- or DHCP-assigned client name, then the MIB2 sysName, then the system's IP address, then, as a last resort, the BOOTP- or DHCP-assigned boot file name. For each filename, the system attempts to read first from the designated defaultFileServer, then, if not successful, from one of either the BOOTP/DHCP server itself or bootconfigFileServerAddr (if specified by the BOOTP/DHCP server).

bootconfigServerConfigTimeout.name: bootconfigServerConfigTimeout
bootconfigServerConfigTimeout.description: The time in seconds which the system should wait for a configuration response from a BOOTP server before falling back to the stored configuration.

bootconfigMultOfferTimeout.name: bootconfigMultOfferTimeout
bootconfigMultOfferTimeout.description: The time, in seconds, which the system should wait for a better offer configuration response from a DHCP or BOOTP server before choosing the best current offer.

bootconfigReqLeaseDuration.name: bootconfigReqLeaseDuration
bootconfigReqLeaseDuration.description: The requested DHCP lease duration, in minutes.

bootconfigMinLeaseDuration.name: bootconfigMinLeaseDuration
bootconfigMinLeaseDuration.description: The minimum acceptable DHCP lease duration, in minutes.

bootconfigDev.name: bootconfigDev
bootconfigDev.description: Text string identifying the network device used for bootstrapping the system via BOOTP or DHCP. This is only applicable in BOOTP mode or when the system is configured as a router, when not all the network interfaces share the same ifPhysAddress.

bootconfigClientAddr.name: bootconfigClientAddr
bootconfigClientAddr.description: IPv4 network address of this device, as determined by the BOOTP or DHCP protocol.

bootconfigHostAddr.name: bootconfigHostAddr
bootconfigHostAddr.description: IPv4 network address of the BOOTP or DHCP server from which the configuration of this device was leased.

bootconfigBootFile.name: bootconfigBootFile
bootconfigBootFile.description: Name of the default boot configuration file, specified by the BOOTP or DHCP server, containing the system configuration to be utilized by this device. This is considered a default configuration file because many DHCP servers are not capable of distinguishing boot files between different clients.

bootconfigSubnetMask.name: bootconfigSubnetMask
bootconfigSubnetMask.description: IPv4 network subnet mask to be used by this device, as determined by the BOOTP or DHCP protocol.

bootconfigGateway.name: bootconfigGateway
bootconfigGateway.description: IPv4 network address of the default network gateway to be used by this device, as determined by the BOOTP or DHCP protocol.

bootconfigHostName.name: bootconfigHostName
bootconfigHostName.description: Textual name of the BOOTP or DHCP server from which the configuration of this device was leased. This should be a DNS-recognizable host name.

bootconfigClientName.name: bootconfigClientName
bootconfigClientName.description: Textual name of this device, as determined by the BOOTP or DHCP protocol. This should be a DNS-recognizable host name.

bootconfigNameServerTable.name: bootconfigNameServerTable
bootconfigNameServerTable.description: Table of DNS Name Servers provided by the bootconfigHostAddr Boot Server.

bootconfigNameServerPriority.name: bootconfigNameServerPriority
bootconfigNameServerPriority.description: The priority order in which a domain name server is queried. Lower values are queried first.

bootconfigNameServer.name: bootconfigNameServer
bootconfigNameServer.description: The IPv4 address of a domain name server.

bootconfigDomainName.name: bootconfigDomainName
bootconfigDomainName.description: Name of the IP domain of which this device is a member, as determined by the BOOTP or DHCP protocol.

bootconfigSntpServer.name: bootconfigSntpServer
bootconfigSntpServer.description: IPv4 network address of SNTP server for use by this device, as determined by the BOOTP or DHCP protocol.

bootconfigSaveServerResponse.name: bootconfigSaveServerResponse
bootconfigSaveServerResponse.description: If true, the leased configuration from a boot server is saved as the new system defaults. If false, system defaults remain unchanged when a new configuration is leased.

bootconfigCmdInvokeIniLoad.name: bootconfigCmdInvokeIniLoad
bootconfigCmdInvokeIniLoad.description: Initiate loading of an initialization script '.ini' file from the file server into the system FLASH. Commands recognized: start.

bootconfigCmdStatusIniLoad.name: bootconfigCmdStatusIniLoad
bootconfigCmdStatusIniLoad.description: Status of the most recent command to load an initialization script '.ini' file. Possible values: 0 = Operation completed successfully (or has not taken place). 2 = The '.ini' file was not found on the file server. 12 = Insufficient memory to load the '.ini' file. 22 = Invalid '.ini' file format. 35 = File format of the '.ini' file is not supported. 68 = Operation is still in progress. Poll again later. 72 = Operation was started, but later was canceled.

bootconfigDhcpClassID.name: bootconfigDhcpClassID
bootconfigDhcpClassID.description: Specification of the DHCP Class Identifier presented by the system when requesting DHCP leases.

bootconfigFileServerAddr.name: bootconfigFileServerAddr
bootconfigFileServerAddr.description: IPv4 network address of the file server from which to read configuration files, as determined by the BOOTP or DHCP protocol.

bootconfigLogServerAddr.name: bootconfigLogServerAddr
bootconfigLogServerAddr.description: IPv4 network address of the host to receive SYSLOG messages, as determined by the BOOTP or DHCP protocol.

bootconfigBootCount.name: bootconfigBootCount
bootconfigBootCount.description: The number of times the system code has been restarted since the system left Cisco manufacturing.

bootconfigDhcpClientIdType.name: bootconfigDhcpClientIdType
bootconfigDhcpClientIdType.description: The ARP hardware type, per RFC 1700, of bootconfigDhcpClientIdValue. If it is not a hardware address (e.g. is a fully-qualified domain name), a value of 0 will be used for the DHCP Client Identifier 'htype' field.

bootconfigDhcpClientIdValue.name: bootconfigDhcpClientIdValue
bootconfigDhcpClientIdValue.description: Specification of the DHCP unique client Identifier presented by the system when requesting DHCP leases.

awcSerialConfigTable.name: awcSerialConfigTable
awcSerialConfigTable.description: SerialConfigTable attributes. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

awcSerialConfigEntry.name: awcSerialConfigEntry
awcSerialConfigEntry.description: An entry in the awcSerialConfigEntry table.

serialDevIndex.name: serialDevIndex
serialDevIndex.description: The index used to access rows in the awcSerialConfig table.

serialAdminStatus.name: serialAdminStatus
serialAdminStatus.description: The requested status of the serial port.

serialOperStatus.name: serialOperStatus
serialOperStatus.description: The actual status of the serial port.

serialBaud.name: serialBaud
serialBaud.description: The baud rate of the serial port.

serialParity.name: serialParity
serialParity.description: The parity of the serial port.

serialDataBits.name: serialDataBits
serialDataBits.description: The number of data bits per character recognized by the serial port.

serialStopBits.name: serialStopBits
serialStopBits.description: The number of stop bits of the serial port.

serialFlowControl.name: serialFlowControl
serialFlowControl.description: The flow control method used by the serial port.

serialTerminalType.name: serialTerminalType
serialTerminalType.description: The terminal type of the serial port.

serialTerminalLines.name: serialTerminalLines
serialTerminalLines.description: The number of horizontal lines available on each terminal page. Default 24.

serialTerminalColumns.name: serialTerminalColumns
serialTerminalColumns.description: The number of vertical columns available on each terminal page. Default 80.

serialDevFd.name: serialDevFd
serialDevFd.description: The VxWorks I/O File Descriptor used to access the serial device.

defaultFileServer.name: defaultFileServer
defaultFileServer.description: The name of the preferred file server to be used for all FTP and TFTP Put and Get operations. Max. name length is 128 octets.

awcFileXferProtocol.name: awcFileXferProtocol
awcFileXferProtocol.description: The protocol to be used by the system for file transfer (TFTP or FTP).

awcFileXferUser.name: awcFileXferUser
awcFileXferUser.description: The name of the user, as required by all FTP file transfers. Max. name length is 128 octets.

awcFileXferPassword.name: awcFileXferPassword
awcFileXferPassword.description: The password of the user, as required by all FTP file transfers. Max. password length is 128 octets.

awcFileXferCmdInvokeFileLoad.name: awcFileXferCmdInvokeFileLoad
awcFileXferCmdInvokeFileLoad.description: Initiate loading of all specified files from the file server into the system FLASH. Commands recognized: start.

awcFileXferCmdStatusFileLoad.name: awcFileXferCmdStatusFileLoad
awcFileXferCmdStatusFileLoad.description: Status of the most recent command to load the specified fileXferFile* files. Possible values: 0 = Operation completed successfully (or has not taken place). 2 = At least one file was not found on the file server. 12 = Insufficient memory to load all files. 22 = No file specified, or invalid file format. 35 = File format of at least one of the files is not supported. 68 = Operation is still in progress. Poll again later. 72 = Operation was started, but later was canceled.

awcFileXferCmdInvokeFileSave.name: awcFileXferCmdInvokeFileSave
awcFileXferCmdInvokeFileSave.description: Initiate saving of all specified fileXferFile* files to the file server from the system FLASH. Commands recognized: start.

awcFileXferCmdStatusFileSave.name: awcFileXferCmdStatusFileSave
awcFileXferCmdStatusFileSave.description: Status of the most recent command to save the specified fileXferFile* files. Possible values: 0 = Operation completed successfully (or has not taken place). 1 = Insufficient permission to save the files. 2 = A directory specified for saving at least one of the files was not found. 22 = No file specified, or invalid file format. 68 = Operation is still in progress. Poll again later. 72 = Operation was started, but later was canceled.

awcFileXferFileFirmwareSystem.name: awcFileXferFileFirmwareSystem
awcFileXferFileFirmwareSystem.description: The filename of the system firmware image. Max. string length is 128 octets.

awcFileXferFileFirmwareRadio0.name: awcFileXferFileFirmwareRadio0
awcFileXferFileFirmwareRadio0.description: The filename of the radio firmware image. Max. string length is 128 octets.

awcFileXferFileWebUI.name: awcFileXferFileWebUI
awcFileXferFileWebUI.description: The filename of the system Web pages image. Max. string length is 128 octets.

awcFileXferFileFpgaPcmcia.name: awcFileXferFileFpgaPcmcia
awcFileXferFileFpgaPcmcia.description: The filename of the FPGA image for the PCMCIA controller. Max. string length is 128 octets.

awcFileXferTftpPort.name: awcFileXferTftpPort
awcFileXferTftpPort.description: IP port number over which to perform TFTP operations. Default 69.

awcFileXferFtpDirectory.name: awcFileXferFtpDirectory
awcFileXferFtpDirectory.description: Directory on defaultFileServer in which files are located.

awcFileXferFilesFLASH.name: awcFileXferFilesFLASH
awcFileXferFilesFLASH.description: The filename of a complete FLASH firmware image for the system, including all non-configuration files within the system FLASH file system. Max. string length is 128 octets.

awcFileXferFileFirmwareRadio1.name: awcFileXferFileFirmwareRadio1
awcFileXferFileFirmwareRadio1.description: The filename of the radio firmware image. Max. string length is 128 octets.

awcIfTable.name: awcIfTable
awcIfTable.description: IfTable attributes. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

awcIfEntry.name: awcIfEntry
awcIfEntry.description: An entry in the awcIfEntry table.

awcIfDefaultPhysAddress.name: awcIfDefaultPhysAddress
awcIfDefaultPhysAddress.description: The default, factory-assigned MAC address of the interface. Guaranteed to be unique across all IEEE 802 devices.

awcIfPhysAddress.name: awcIfPhysAddress
awcIfPhysAddress.description: The MAC address to be used by the interface. If awcIfDefaultPhysAddress is to be used, this is 00:00:00:00:00:00.

awcIfAdoptPrimaryIdentity.name: awcIfAdoptPrimaryIdentity
awcIfAdoptPrimaryIdentity.description: If true, this interface adopts the identity of bootconfigDev, the primary interface. This includes MAC address, IP address, etc. This is the conventional mode of operation when operating as a transparent bridge. If false, this interface always has a unique MAC address.

awcIfDefaultIpAddress.name: awcIfDefaultIpAddress
awcIfDefaultIpAddress.description: The default IPv4 Address of the interface. If BOOTP or DHCP is enabled, this may be overridden by the BOOTP or DHCP server.

awcIfDefaultIpNetMask.name: awcIfDefaultIpNetMask
awcIfDefaultIpNetMask.description: The default IPv4 netmask of the interface. If BOOTP or DHCP is enabled, this may be overridden by the BOOTP or DHCP server.

awcIfIpAddress.name: awcIfIpAddress
awcIfIpAddress.description: The IPv4 Address currently in use by the interface.

awcIfIpNetMask.name: awcIfIpNetMask
awcIfIpNetMask.description: The IPv4 netmask currently in use by the interface.

awcIfMSDUMaxLength.name: awcIfMSDUMaxLength
awcIfMSDUMaxLength.description: Maximum length of the data portion of a packet for this particular interface. This is the maximum MAC Service Data Unit length, which is greater than or equal to ifMtu, depending on the configured MAC-level encapsulation.

awcIfOutDiscardsCoS0.name: awcIfOutDiscardsCoS0
awcIfOutDiscardsCoS0.description: The number of outbound packets of CoS 0 which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. Another reason would be exceeding their maximum time-to-live.

awcIfOutDiscardsCoS1.name: awcIfOutDiscardsCoS1
awcIfOutDiscardsCoS1.description: The number of outbound packets of CoS 1 which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. Another reason would be exceeding their maximum time-to-live.

awcIfOutDiscardsCoS2.name: awcIfOutDiscardsCoS2
awcIfOutDiscardsCoS2.description: The number of outbound packets of CoS 2 which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. Another reason would be exceeding their maximum time-to-live.

awcIfOutDiscardsCoS3.name: awcIfOutDiscardsCoS3
awcIfOutDiscardsCoS3.description: The number of outbound packets of CoS 3 which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. Another reason would be exceeding their maximum time-to-live.

awcIfOutDiscardsCoS4.name: awcIfOutDiscardsCoS4
awcIfOutDiscardsCoS4.description: The number of outbound packets of CoS 4 which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. Another reason would be exceeding their maximum time-to-live.

awcIfOutDiscardsCoS5.name: awcIfOutDiscardsCoS5
awcIfOutDiscardsCoS5.description: The number of outbound packets of CoS 5 which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. Another reason would be exceeding their maximum time-to-live.

awcIfOutDiscardsCoS6.name: awcIfOutDiscardsCoS6
awcIfOutDiscardsCoS6.description: The number of outbound packets of CoS 6 which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. Another reason would be exceeding their maximum time-to-live.

awcIfOutDiscardsCoS7.name: awcIfOutDiscardsCoS7
awcIfOutDiscardsCoS7.description: The number of outbound packets of CoS 7 which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. Another reason would be exceeding their maximum time-to-live.

awcDot11StationConfigTable.name: awcDot11StationConfigTable
awcDot11StationConfigTable.description: Station Config Table attributes. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

awcDot11StationConfigEntry.name: awcDot11StationConfigEntry
awcDot11StationConfigEntry.description: An entry in the awcDot11StationConfigTable table.

awcDot11StationRole.name: awcDot11StationRole
awcDot11StationRole.description: The role of this station itself within the 802.11 BSS (radio cell) of which it is a member.

awcDot11PowerManagementSubMode.name: awcDot11PowerManagementSubMode
awcDot11PowerManagementSubMode.description: When configured as roleClient, the Power Management Submode of the device.

awcDot11UseAWCExtensions.name: awcDot11UseAWCExtensions
awcDot11UseAWCExtensions.description: If true, Aironet extensions to the basic 802.11 protocol are enabled. This results in better BSS performance and faster roaming. If false, only the basic 802.11 protocols are used. This ensures maximum compatibility with non-Aironet equipment.

awcDot11AllowAssocBroadcastSSID.name: awcDot11AllowAssocBroadcastSSID
awcDot11AllowAssocBroadcastSSID.description: If true and awcDot11StationRole is either roleAP or roleRepeater, the radio will respond to Broadcast SSID Probe Requests and will broadcast its own SSID within its Beacons. If false, the radio will not respond to the Broadcast SSID and will not broadcast its SSID within Beacons.

awcDot11PrivacyOptionImplementedMaxRate.name: awcDot11PrivacyOptionImplementedMaxRate
awcDot11PrivacyOptionImplementedMaxRate.description: The maximum Transmit bit rate supported by the radio when using WEP encryption. Expressed in standard 802.11 increments of 500Kb/sec.

awcDot11DesiredBSSLength.name: awcDot11DesiredBSSLength
awcDot11DesiredBSSLength.description: The number of entries in awcDot11DesiredBSSTable.

awcDot11EnetEncapsulationDefault.name: awcDot11EnetEncapsulationDefault
awcDot11EnetEncapsulationDefault.description: The Ethernet Encapsulation Transform type used within the BSS. Either IEEE 802.1H or RFC 1042 can be utilized. IEEE 802.1H provides exceptions for the Novel IPX and AARP protocols.

awcDot11ForceReqFirmwareVersion.name: awcDot11ForceReqFirmwareVersion
awcDot11ForceReqFirmwareVersion.description: If true, the radio driver will only allow operation with the specific radio firmware revision with which it was originally tested. If false, the radio driver will allow operation with the radio firmware revision with which it was tested, or any later radio firmware revision.

awcDot11BridgeSpacing.name: awcDot11BridgeSpacing
awcDot11BridgeSpacing.description: If this device is the root side of a Bridge configuration, this value is the distance in kilometers reported between this device and its farthest non-root Bridge.

awcDot11DesiredSSIDMaxAssociatedSTA.name: awcDot11DesiredSSIDMaxAssociatedSTA
awcDot11DesiredSSIDMaxAssociatedSTA.description: The maximum number of 802.11 Stations which may Associate with this access point through either the Broadcast SSID or through dot11DesiredSSID. If 0, the maximum number is limited only by the 802.11 standard and by any hardware or radio firmware limitations of the access point.

awcDot11DesiredSSIDNumAssociatedSTA.name: awcDot11DesiredSSIDNumAssociatedSTA
awcDot11DesiredSSIDNumAssociatedSTA.description: The current number of 802.11 Stations which are Associated with this access point through either the Broadcast SSID or through dot11DesiredSSID.

awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDLength.name: awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDLength
awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDLength.description: The maximum number of entries in awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDTable. If awcDot11MultipleSSIDPerBSSImplemented is FALSE, awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDLength must be 0.

awcDot11MultipleSSIDPerBSSImplemented.name: awcDot11MultipleSSIDPerBSSImplemented
awcDot11MultipleSSIDPerBSSImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the station implementation is capable of responding to 802.11 Probe Requests for SSIDs other than dot11DesiredSSID. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

awcDot11SymbolExtensionsImplemented.name: awcDot11SymbolExtensionsImplemented
awcDot11SymbolExtensionsImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the station implementation is capable of generating Symbol, Inc. proprietary elements in its Beacons and Probe Responses. These elements enable support for Symbol Voice-over-IP (VoIP) phones. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

awcDot11SymbolExtensionsEnabled.name: awcDot11SymbolExtensionsEnabled
awcDot11SymbolExtensionsEnabled.description: Should the Radio generate Symbol, Inc. proprietary elements in its Beacons and Probe Responses in support of Symbol VoIP phones?

awcDot11DesiredSSIDMicAlgorithm.name: awcDot11DesiredSSIDMicAlgorithm
awcDot11DesiredSSIDMicAlgorithm.description: Auxiliary Message Integrity Check (MIC) calculated on WEP-encoded packets of stations Associated to this access point through either the Broadcast SSID or dot11DesiredSSID.

awcDot11DesiredSSIDWEPKeyPermuteAlgorith.name: awcDot11DesiredSSIDWEPKeyPermuteAlgorithm
awcDot11DesiredSSIDWEPKeyPermuteAlgorith.description: Function through which the WEP encryption key is permuted between key renewal periods for stations Associated to this access point through either the Broadcast SSID or dot11DesiredSSID.

awcDot11DesiredSSIDInfrastructureWGB.name: awcDot11DesiredSSIDInfrastructureWGB
awcDot11DesiredSSIDInfrastructureWGB.description: When true, Workgroup Bridge-class devices Associated to this access point through either the Broadcast SSID or dot11DesiredSSID are provided the class of service which is provided to network infrastructure stations by their parent access point. This includes use of the 802.11 reliable multicast protocol (4-address packets for multicast). When false, Workgroup Bridge-class devices are provided the class of service which is provided to ordinary client stations.

awcDot11DesiredSSIDDefaultPolId.name: awcDot11DesiredSSIDDefaultPolId
awcDot11DesiredSSIDDefaultPolId.description: Default Policy Group Identifier for stations Associated to this access point through either the Broadcast SSID or dot11DesiredSSID. A value of 0 indicates that no special policies are to be applied by default.

awcDot11DesiredSSIDDefaultVlanId.name: awcDot11DesiredSSIDDefaultVlanId
awcDot11DesiredSSIDDefaultVlanId.description: Default VLAN Identifier for stations Associated to this access point through either the Broadcast SSID or dot11DesiredSSID. A value of 0 indicates that either VLANs are disabled or that the default VLAN is awcNativeVlanId.

awcDot11DesiredSSIDEnableProxyMobileIP.name: awcDot11DesiredSSIDEnableProxyMobileIP
awcDot11DesiredSSIDEnableProxyMobileIP.description: If true, Proxy Mobile IP is enabled for use by all stations Associated to this access point through either the Broadcast SSID or dot11DesiredSSID.

awcDot11InfrastructureSSID.name: awcDot11InfrastructureSSID
awcDot11InfrastructureSSID.description: Index of the SSID which all 802.11 infrastructure stations shall use for Association. If 0, an access point and its repeaters and other subordinate infrastructure devices will Associate through dot11DesiredSSID. If non-0, an access point and its subordinate infrastructure devices will Associate through the auxiliary SSID with awcDot11AuxSSIDIndex equal to awcDot11InfrastructureSSID.

awcDot11QBSSElementImplemented.name: awcDot11QBSSElementImplemented
awcDot11QBSSElementImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the station implementation is capable of generating 802.11e QBSS elements in its Beacons and Probe Responses. These elements enable support for basic 802.11 Quality of Service. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

awcDot11QBSSElementEnabled.name: awcDot11QBSSElementEnabled
awcDot11QBSSElementEnabled.description: Should the Radio generate 802.11e QBSS elements in its Beacons and Probe Responses in support of 802.11 Quality of Service?

awcDot11InfrastructureSSIDExclusive.name: awcDot11InfrastructureSSIDExclusive
awcDot11InfrastructureSSIDExclusive.description: Should this access point restrict all infrastructure stations to associate only through the SSID specified by awcDot11InfrastructureSSID?

awcDot11SendIGMPGeneralQuery.name: awcDot11SendIGMPGeneralQuery
awcDot11SendIGMPGeneralQuery.description: Should this access point issue an IGMP General Query to all associated stations when they complete all required high-level authentication? Such an IGMP query can help configure multicast groups efficiently.

awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable.name: awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable
awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, section 5.7.6 and IEEE802dot11-MIB.
awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable.description: This table contains attributes to configure authentication algorithm parameters for associations through the SSID defined by IEEE802dot11-MIB dot11DesiredSSID object. It defines attributes additional to those defined in the IEEE802dot11-MIB dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable. An interface may support multiple authentication algorithms. This table has an expansion dependent relationship on the ifTable. For each entry in this table, there exists at least an entry in the ifTable of ifType ieee80211(71). This table uses the dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex of the dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable defined in the IEEE802dot11-MIB as the expansion index. Entries in this table cannot be created or deleted by the network management system. All entries are created or deleted by the agent.

awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEntry.name: awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEntry
awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEntry.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, section 8.2 and IEEE802dot11-MIB.
awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEntry.description: Each entry specifies Cisco Aironet product specific authentication algorithm configuration attributes of the dot11DesiredSSID on a radio interface.

awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex.name: awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex
awcDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the Aironet Authentication Algorithms Table. This variable corresponds directly to the 802.11 dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex.

awcDot11AuthenticationRequireEAP.name: awcDot11AuthenticationRequireEAP
awcDot11AuthenticationRequireEAP.description: If true, stations authenticating with the corresponding dot11AuthenticationAlgorithm must complete network-level EAP authentication before they will be unblocked. If false, stations authenticating with the corresponding dot11AuthenticationAlgorithm will be unblocked as soon as they complete the requirements of 802.11 authentication.

awcDot11AuthenticationDefaultUcastAllowe.name: awcDot11AuthenticationDefaultUcastAllowedToGoTo
awcDot11AuthenticationDefaultUcastAllowe.description: The set of ports to which frames received from a specific port and destined for a MAC address which is not already listed in dot1dStaticTable and authenticates with the corresponding dot11AuthenticationAlgorithm, are allowed to be forwarded. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. (Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant.) The default value of this object is a string of ones of appropriate length.

awcDot11WEPDefaultKeysTable.name: awcDot11WEPDefaultKeysTable
awcDot11WEPDefaultKeysTable.description: Extension of dot11WEPDefaultKeysTable to allow for key lengths other than 40 bits.

awcDot11WEPDefaultKeysEntry.name: awcDot11WEPDefaultKeysEntry
awcDot11WEPDefaultKeysEntry.description: An entry in the awcDot11WEPDefaultKeysTable table.

awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyIndex.name: awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyIndex
awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the WEP Default Keys Table. The value of this variable is equal to the WEPDefaultKeyID + 1

awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyLen.name: awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyLen
awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyLen.description: Length in octets of awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyValue. If 0, the corresponding awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyValue is not configured.

awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyValue.name: awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyValue
awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyValue.description: A WEP default secret key value. The value is write-only (attempt to read will result in return of a zero-length string).

awcDot11PrivacyTable.name: awcDot11PrivacyTable
awcDot11PrivacyTable.description: Additional information about the WEP capabilities of the device. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

awcDot11PrivacyEntry.name: awcDot11PrivacyEntry
awcDot11PrivacyEntry.description: An entry in the awcDot11PrivacyTable table.

awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyMaxIndex.name: awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyMaxIndex
awcDot11WEPDefaultKeyMaxIndex.description: The maximum WEP Default Key index which the radio supports. Range 1..4, or 0 if the radio does not support WEP.

awcDot11AllowEncrypted.name: awcDot11AllowEncrypted
awcDot11AllowEncrypted.description: When this attribute is true, the STA shall indicate at the MAC service interface received MSDUs regardless of the setting of the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field, so long as the dot11ExcludeUnencrypted attribute is false. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

awcDot11WEPKeyMaxLen.name: awcDot11WEPKeyMaxLen
awcDot11WEPKeyMaxLen.description: The maximum WEP Key Length which the radio supports. Range 0..16, or 0 if the radio does not support WEP. Note that, even if the radio supports more than 13 octets of key value, the current 802.11 standard only makes use of the first 13 octets.

awcDot11LEAPUserName.name: awcDot11LEAPUserName
awcDot11LEAPUserName.description: User Name assigned to the system for use when authenticating with AAA servers.

awcDot11LEAPPassword.name: awcDot11LEAPPassword
awcDot11LEAPPassword.description: User Password (shared secret) assigned to the system for use when authenticating with AAA servers.

awcDot11DesiredBSSTable.name: awcDot11DesiredBSSTable
awcDot11DesiredBSSTable.description: When the radio is not in roleAP, a list of preferred Access Points with which the radio should Associate. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

awcDot11DesiredBSSEntry.name: awcDot11DesiredBSSEntry
awcDot11DesiredBSSEntry.description: An entry in the awcDot11DesiredBSSTable table.

awcDot11DesiredBSSIndex.name: awcDot11DesiredBSSIndex
awcDot11DesiredBSSIndex.description: The priority order in which Preferred Access Points should be probed. Lower indices are probed first.

awcDot11DesiredBSS.name: awcDot11DesiredBSS
awcDot11DesiredBSS.description: The BSS identifier (MAC address) of the Access Point with which the radio should try to Associate, or 00:00:00:00:00:00 if the BSS identifier for this priority is unspecified.

awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDTable.name: awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDTable
awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDTable.description: When the radio is not in roleClient, a list of Stations which, when Associated to this system, shall always have the same AID.

awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDEntry.name: awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDEntry
awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDEntry.description: An entry in the awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDTable table.

awcDot11AuxSSIDIndex.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDIndex
awcDot11AuxSSIDIndex.description: Identifier of auxiliary SSIDs supported by the access point in addition to dot11DesiredSSID. Domain from 1 to awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDLength.

awcDot11AuxSSID.name: awcDot11AuxSSID
awcDot11AuxSSID.description: This attribute reflects a Service Set ID recognized by the access point. The access point shall respond to Probe Requests specifying this SSID, but does not advertise this SSID in its Beacons.

awcDot11AuxSSIDMaxAssociatedSTA.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDMaxAssociatedSTA
awcDot11AuxSSIDMaxAssociatedSTA.description: The maximum number of 802.11 Stations which may Associate with this access point through awcDot11AuxSSID. If 0, the maximum number is limited only by the 802.11 standard and by any hardware or radio firmware limitations of the access point.

awcDot11AuxSSIDNumAssociatedSTA.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDNumAssociatedSTA
awcDot11AuxSSIDNumAssociatedSTA.description: The current number of 802.11 Stations which are Associated with this access point through awcDot11AuxSSID.

awcDot11AuxSSIDDefaultPolId.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDDefaultPolId
awcDot11AuxSSIDDefaultPolId.description: Default Policy Group Identifier for stations Associated to this access point over awcDot11AuxSSID. A value of 0 indicates that no special policies are to be applied by default.

awcDot11AuxSSIDDefaultVlanId.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDDefaultVlanId
awcDot11AuxSSIDDefaultVlanId.description: Default VLAN Identifier for stations Associated to this access point over awcDot11AuxSSID. A value of 0 indicates that either VLANs are disabled or that the default VLAN is awcNativeVlanId.

awcDot11AuxSSIDEnableProxyMobileIP.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDEnableProxyMobileIP
awcDot11AuxSSIDEnableProxyMobileIP.description: If true, Proxy Mobile IP is enabled for use by all stations Associated to this access point over awcDot11AuxSSID.

awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgTable.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgTable
awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgTable.description: This (conceptual) table of attributes shall be a set of all the Aironet-specific parameters for each authentication algorithm supported by the station for each auxiliary SSID listed in awcDot11AuxiliarySSIDTable.

awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgEntry.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgEntry
awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the Aironet Auxiliary SSID Authentication Algorithms Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgIndex.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgIndex
awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the Aironet Auxiliary SSID Authentication Algorithms Table. This variable corresponds directly to the 802.11 dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex.

awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgEnable.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgEnable
awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgEnable.description: If true, stations may authenticate to the SSID specified by awcDot11AuxSSIDIndex with the algorithm corresponding to dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex.

awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgRequireEAP.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgRequireEAP
awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgRequireEAP.description: If true, stations authenticating to the SSID specified by awcDot11AuxSSIDIndex with the corresponding dot11AuthenticationAlgorithm must complete network-level EAP authentication before they will be unblocked. If false, stations authenticating with the corresponding dot11AuthenticationAlgorithm will be unblocked as soon as they complete the requirements of 802.11 authentication.

awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgDefaultUcastAllowe.name: awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgDefaultUcastAllowedToGoTo
awcDot11AuxSSIDAuthAlgDefaultUcastAllowe.description: The set of ports to which frames received from a specific port and destined for a MAC address which is not already listed in dot1dStaticTable and authenticates to the SSID specified by awcDot11AuxSSIDIndex with the corresponding dot11AuthenticationAlgorithm, are allowed to be forwarded. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. (Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant.) The default value of this object is a string of ones of appropriate length.

awcDot11AssignedAIDTable.name: awcDot11AssignedAIDTable
awcDot11AssignedAIDTable.description: When the radio is not functioning as a client station (i.e., awcDot11StationRole is not 'roleClient'), this is the list of AIDs which this agent will assign to the clients associating with it. An AID is assigned if the corresponding MAC address matches that of the client. This table has an expansion dependent relationship on the ifTable. For each entry in this table, there exists at least an entry in the ifTable of ifType ieee80211(71).

awcDot11AssignedAIDEntry.name: awcDot11AssignedAIDEntry
awcDot11AssignedAIDEntry.description: An entry in the awcDot11AssignedAIDTable table.

awcDot11AssignedAID.name: awcDot11AssignedAID
awcDot11AssignedAID.description: An AID which shall be reserved for the exclusive use of a single Station.

awcDot11AssignedSTA.name: awcDot11AssignedSTA
awcDot11AssignedSTA.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, section 5.7.2.
awcDot11AssignedSTA.description: The Station (MAC address) which, when Associated to this system, shall always be assigned awcDot11AssignedAID as its 802.11 AID.

awcDot11AccessPointCountersTable.name: awcDot11AccessPointCountersTable
awcDot11AccessPointCountersTable.description: This table includes radio statistics collected by the IEEE 802.11 radio interface. This table has a sparse dependent relationship on the ifTable. For each entry in this table, there exists an entry in the ifTable of ifType ieee80211(71).

awcDot11AccessPointCountersEntry.name: awcDot11AccessPointCountersEntry
awcDot11AccessPointCountersEntry.description: Each entry contains counters of frame transmissions and client associations for a radio interface.

awcDot11AssociatedStationCount.name: awcDot11AssociatedStationCount
awcDot11AssociatedStationCount.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, section 5.7.
awcDot11AssociatedStationCount.description: Total number of successful 802.11 Association Request operations to this radio of this access point since system startup.

awcDot11AuthenticatedStationCount.name: awcDot11AuthenticatedStationCount
awcDot11AuthenticatedStationCount.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, section 5.7.
awcDot11AuthenticatedStationCount.description: Total number of successful 802.11 MAC-level Authentication operations to this radio of this access point since system startup.

awcDot11ReassociatedStationCount.name: awcDot11ReassociatedStationCount
awcDot11ReassociatedStationCount.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, section 5.7.
awcDot11ReassociatedStationCount.description: Total number of successful 802.11 Reassociation Request operations to this radio of this access point since system startup.

awcDot11RoamedStationCount.name: awcDot11RoamedStationCount
awcDot11RoamedStationCount.description: Total number of times that clients which had successfully (re)associated with this access point successfully reassociated with another access point since system startup.

awcDot11DeauthenticateCount.name: awcDot11DeauthenticateCount
awcDot11DeauthenticateCount.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, section 5.7.
awcDot11DeauthenticateCount.description: Total number of Deauthenticate frames sent over this radio of this access point since system startup.

awcDot11DisassociateCount.name: awcDot11DisassociateCount
awcDot11DisassociateCount.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, section 5.7.
awcDot11DisassociateCount.description: Total number of Disassociate frames sent over this radio of this access point since system startup.

awcDot11EncapPktsMMH.name: awcDot11EncapPktsMMH
awcDot11EncapPktsMMH.description: Total number of packets for which the a MIC has been requested to be calculated with the MMH algorithm before being submitted for transmission over this radio of this access point since system startup.

awcDot11DecapPktsMMH.name: awcDot11DecapPktsMMH
awcDot11DecapPktsMMH.description: Total number of packets received over this radio of this access point since system startup and for which a MIC has been requested to be validated with the MMH algorithm.

awcDot11EncapErrorsMMH.name: awcDot11EncapErrorsMMH
awcDot11EncapErrorsMMH.description: Total number of packets which have failed MIC calculation with the MMH algorithm before being submitted for transmission over this radio of this access point since system startup.

awcDot11DecapErrorsMMH.name: awcDot11DecapErrorsMMH
awcDot11DecapErrorsMMH.description: Total number of packets received over this radio of this access point since system startup which have failed MIC validation with the MMH algorithm.

awcDot11DecapExistsMMH.name: awcDot11DecapExistsMMH
awcDot11DecapExistsMMH.description: Total number of packets received over this radio of this access point since system startup which have failed MIC validation with the MMH algorithm specifically due to sequence number and duplicate packet errors.

awcDot11DecapAccessMMH.name: awcDot11DecapAccessMMH
awcDot11DecapAccessMMH.description: Total number of packets received over this radio of this access point since system startup which have failed MIC validation with the MMH algorithm specifically due to cryptographic key-mismatch errors.

awcDot11CountersTable.name: awcDot11CountersTable
awcDot11CountersTable.description: This table contains MAC statistics on each of IEEE 802.11 interface. This table has a sparse dependent relationship on the ifTable. For each entry in this table, there exists an entry in the ifTable of ifType ieee80211(71).

awcDot11CountersEntry.name: awcDot11CountersEntry
awcDot11CountersEntry.description: Each entry contains counters of frame transmissions for a radio interface.

awcDot11TxDeferEnergyCount.name: awcDot11TxDeferEnergyCount
awcDot11TxDeferEnergyCount.description: Total number of frames deferred transmission due to energy detect since system startup.

awcDot11RxMacCrcErrorCount.name: awcDot11RxMacCrcErrorCount
awcDot11RxMacCrcErrorCount.description: Total number of frames received with MAC CRC errors since system startup.

awcDot11SsidMismatchCount.name: awcDot11SsidMismatchCount
awcDot11SsidMismatchCount.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, IEEE802dot11-MIB.
awcDot11SsidMismatchCount.description: Total number of Beacon or Probe Response frames received for which the SSID does not match dot11DesiredSSID since system startup.

awcDot11QoSTable.name: awcDot11QoSTable
awcDot11QoSTable.description: This (conceptual) table of attributes shall be a set of parameters for each traffic category (i.e. 802.1D priority) of packet passed over the radio.

awcDot11QoSEntry.name: awcDot11QoSEntry
awcDot11QoSEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the Aironet Quality of Service Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

awcDot11QoSCoS.name: awcDot11QoSCoS
awcDot11QoSCoS.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the Aironet Quality of Service Table. This variable corresponds directly to the 802.1D traffic category ID, plus 1.

awcDot11QoSCWmin.name: awcDot11QoSCWmin
awcDot11QoSCWmin.description: 802.11 CWmin of the traffic category. The value of this OID must be one of the set 0, 1, 3, 7, 15, 31, 63, 127, 255, 511, or 1023, and must be less than or equal to awcDot11QoSCWmax.

awcDot11QoSCWmax.name: awcDot11QoSCWmax
awcDot11QoSCWmax.description: 802.11 CWmax of the traffic category. The value of this OID must be one of the set 1, 3, 7, 15, 31, 63, 127, 255, 511, or 1023, and must be greater than or equal to awcDot11QoSCWmin.

awcDot11ResourceInfoTable.name: awcDot11ResourceInfoTable
awcDot11ResourceInfoTable.description: Resource Info Table attributes. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

awcDot11ResourceInfoEntry.name: awcDot11ResourceInfoEntry
awcDot11ResourceInfoEntry.description: An entry in the awcDot11ResourceInfoTable table.

awcDot11FirmwareBootstrapVersion.name: awcDot11FirmwareBootstrapVersion
awcDot11FirmwareBootstrapVersion.description: The firmware version of the radio boot block. Max. string length is 128 octets.

awcDot11PhyOperationTable.name: awcDot11PhyOperationTable
awcDot11PhyOperationTable.description: awcDot11PhyOperationTable attributes. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

awcDot11PhyOperationEntry.name: awcDot11PhyOperationEntry
awcDot11PhyOperationEntry.description: An entry in the awcDot11PhyOperationTable table.

awcDot11CurrentCarrierSet.name: awcDot11CurrentCarrierSet
awcDot11CurrentCarrierSet.description: The carrier set of the device. The Carrier Set implies a Regulatory Domain, but geographic-specific restrictions within a Regulatory Domain may necessitate several Carrier Sets within the Regulatory Domain.

awcDot11ModulationType.name: awcDot11ModulationType
awcDot11ModulationType.description: The RF modulation of the radio.

awcDot11PreambleType.name: awcDot11PreambleType
awcDot11PreambleType.description: The current radio preamble type in use by the Station. Possible values: 1 = Use long preambles whenever possible. 2 = Use only short preambles.

awcDot11PHYType.name: awcDot11PHYType
awcDot11PHYType.description: This is an 8-bit integer value that identifies the PHY type supported by the attached PLCP and PMD. Currently defined values and their corresponding PHY types are: FHSS 2.4 GHz = 01 , DSSS 2.4 GHz = 02, IR Baseband = 03, DSSS 5.0 GHz = 11

awcDot11PhyFHSSTable.name: awcDot11PhyFHSSTable
awcDot11PhyFHSSTable.description: awcDot11PhyFHSSTable attributes. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

awcDot11PhyFHSSEntry.name: awcDot11PhyFHSSEntry
awcDot11PhyFHSSEntry.description: An entry in the awcDot11PhyFHSSTable table.

awcDot11Compatible3100.name: awcDot11Compatible3100
awcDot11Compatible3100.description: Boolean on whether or not the Station should use 1Mb/sec management frames to be compatible with Aironet 3100 series radios.

awcDot11PhyDSSSTable.name: awcDot11PhyDSSSTable
awcDot11PhyDSSSTable.description: awcDot11PhyDSSSTable attributes. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

awcDot11PhyDSSSEntry.name: awcDot11PhyDSSSEntry
awcDot11PhyDSSSEntry.description: An entry in the awcDot11PhyDSSSTable table.

awcDot11Compatible4500.name: awcDot11Compatible4500
awcDot11Compatible4500.description: Boolean on whether or not the Station should use 2Mb/sec management frames to be compatible with Aironet 4500 series radios.

awcDot11ChannelAutoImplemented.name: awcDot11ChannelAutoImplemented
awcDot11ChannelAutoImplemented.description: If true, the radio can, when awcDot11StationRole is roleAP, scan for other BSS activity on all channels available in the current awcDot11CurrentCarrierSet before establishing its own BSS. If false, the radio can only establish its BSS on dot11CurrentChannel.

awcDot11ChannelAutoEnabled.name: awcDot11ChannelAutoEnabled
awcDot11ChannelAutoEnabled.description: If true and awcDot11StationRole is roleAP, the radio will scan for other BSS activity on all channels available in the current awcDot11CurrentCarrierSet before establishing its own BSS. After the scan, this station will establish its own BSS on the channel it considers to have the least probability of congestion. If false, this station always establishes its BSS on dot11CurrentChannel.

awcDot11CurrentChannel.name: awcDot11CurrentChannel
awcDot11CurrentChannel.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, IEEE802dot11-MIB.
awcDot11CurrentChannel.description: The current operating frequency channel of the DSSS PHY, as selected either by selective scanning or via dot11CurrentChannel. Valid channel numbers are as defined in 15.4.6.2

awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyTable.name: awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyTable
awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyTable.description: For each transmit and receive bit rate, whether or not the radio can support WEP encryption at that rate.

awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyEntry.name: awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyEntry
awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacy Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyIndex.name: awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyIndex
awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyIndex.description: Index object which identifies which data rate to access. Range is 1..8.

awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyValue.name: awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyValue
awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyValue.description: The receive or transmit bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from X02-X7f, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500Kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s.

awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyImpleme.name: awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyImplemented
awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyImpleme.description: Whether or not WEP encryption is supported by the radio for both Transmit and Receive operations at the corresponding bit rate specified by awcDot11SupportedDataRatesPrivacyValue.

awcDot11ChanSelectTable.name: awcDot11ChanSelectTable
awcDot11ChanSelectTable.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, section 15.4.6.2.
awcDot11ChanSelectTable.description: This table specifies for each 802.11 channel, whether the scanning process controlled by the awcDot11ChannelAutoEnabled can select a particular channel for use. This table has an expansion dependent relationship on the ifTable. For each entry in this table, there exists at least an entry in the ifTable of ifType ieee80211(71). Entries in this table cannot be created or deleted by the network management system. All entries are created or deleted by the agent.

awcDot11ChanSelectEntry.name: awcDot11ChanSelectEntry
awcDot11ChanSelectEntry.description: Each entry specifies if a particular radio channel is enabled on a radio interface.

awcDot11ChanSelectChannel.name: awcDot11ChanSelectChannel
awcDot11ChanSelectChannel.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, section 15.4.6.2.
awcDot11ChanSelectChannel.description: 802.11 channel which is a candidate for low-occupancy scanning.

awcDot11ChanSelectEnable.name: awcDot11ChanSelectEnable
awcDot11ChanSelectEnable.reference: IEEE Std 802.11-Jan 14 1999, Wireless LAN Medium Access Control and Physical Layer Specifications, LAN MAN Standards Committee of the IEEE Computer Society, IEEE802dot11-MIB.
awcDot11ChanSelectEnable.description: If true, awcDot11ChanSelectChannel is available for the system to use as its awcDot11CurrentChannel after scanning for channel occupancy. If false, awcDot11ChanSelectChannel is not available.

userMgrConfigEntry.name: userMgrConfigEntry
userMgrConfigEntry.description: An entry in the user manager table.

userMgrUserName.name: userMgrUserName
userMgrUserName.description: The name of the user. This should be unique across all users. Max. string length is 32 octets.

userMgrPassword.name: userMgrPassword
userMgrPassword.description: The SHA-1 hashed password of the user in the user manager. When a plaintext password is written, it is automatically replaced by the SHA-1 Secure Hash of that plaintext, prefixed by a 4-octet magic cookie. Max. string length is 24 octets.

userMgrCapabilities.name: userMgrCapabilities
userMgrCapabilities.description: Bitmask of the capabilities of the user. The value may be any combination (sum) of the following capability values: 0 = none 1 = Administrator 2 = Write 4 = Firmware Update 8 = Identity Update 16 = SNMP Community

userMgrStatus.name: userMgrStatus
userMgrStatus.description: Row status of the user. Allows deletion via SNMP.

enableUserMgr.name: enableUserMgr
enableUserMgr.description: If true, the User Manager subsystem is active. Web page, console, and SNMP access is restricted in accordance with userMgrCapabilities. If false, all users have full access to the system.

allowBrowseWithoutLogin.name: allowBrowseWithoutLogin
allowBrowseWithoutLogin.description: If true, the HTTP user interface to read-only web pages can be accessed without passing HTTP authentication. If false, any HTTP access requires the user to pass HTTP authentication.

protectLegalPage.name: protectLegalPage
protectLegalPage.description: Should the legal credits page be protected or not.

defaultWebRoot.name: defaultWebRoot
defaultWebRoot.description: File directory which contains the system's web site root file index.shm. Max. string length is 128 octets.

defaultHelpRoot.name: defaultHelpRoot
defaultHelpRoot.description: URL identifying the directory in which help pages for the system are located. This URL is prefixed to all help page links. Max. string length is 128 octets.

getWebUI.name: getWebUI
getWebUI.description: The name of an auxilliary set of HTML user interface files to be loaded at system boot time from defaultFileServer. Archive formats accepted include .tar and .tar.gz. Max. string length is 128 octets.

cmdInvokeGetWebUI.name: cmdInvokeGetWebUI
cmdInvokeGetWebUI.description: Initiate loading of the getWebUI file. Commands recognized: start.

cmdStatusGetWebUI.name: cmdStatusGetWebUI
cmdStatusGetWebUI.description: Status of the most recent command to load the auxilliary web User Interface pages. Possible values: 0 = Operation completed successfully (or has not taken place). 2 = File not found on the file server. 12 = Insufficient memory to load all files. 20 = Identifier encountered while decoding is an ordinary file, not a directory. 22 = No file specified, or invalid file format. 35 = File format is not supported. 68 = Operation is still in progress. Poll again later. 72 = Operation was started, but later was canceled.

awcHttpdPort.name: awcHttpdPort
awcHttpdPort.description: IP port number over which to perform HTTP operations.

awcConsoleAutoApply.name: awcConsoleAutoApply
awcConsoleAutoApply.description: The current state of 'auto apply' mode on the console browser.

resolverDomain.name: resolverDomain
resolverDomain.description: The name of the resolver domain currently in use by the system. Max. string length of 128 octets.

resolverDomainSuffix.name: resolverDomainSuffix
resolverDomainSuffix.description: The suffix name of the resolver domain. Used to abbreviate displayed host names. Max. string length is 128 octets.

resolverDomainServerTable.name: resolverDomainServerTable
resolverDomainServerTable.description: Table of DNS Name Servers currently in use by the system.

resolverDomainServerPriority.name: resolverDomainServerPriority
resolverDomainServerPriority.description: The priority order in which a domain name server is queried.

resolverDomainServer.name: resolverDomainServer
resolverDomainServer.description: The IP Address of a domain name server currently in use by the system.

defaultResolverDomain.name: defaultResolverDomain
defaultResolverDomain.description: The name of the resolver domain to be used by the system unless overridden by a BOOTP or DHCP server. Max. string length of 128 octets.

defaultResolverDomainServerTable.name: defaultResolverDomainServerTable
defaultResolverDomainServerTable.description: Table of DNS Name Servers to be used by the system unless overridden by a BOOTP or DHCP server.

defaultResolverDomainServerPriority.name: defaultResolverDomainServerPriority
defaultResolverDomainServerPriority.description: The priority order in which a domain name server is queried.

defaultResolverDomainServer.name: defaultResolverDomainServer
defaultResolverDomainServer.description: The IP Address of a domain name server to be used by the system unless overridden by a BOOTP or DHCP server.

snmpTrapDest.name: snmpTrapDest
snmpTrapDest.description: The destination of an SNMP trap. This may be any DNS-recognizable IP address. Max. string length is 128 octets.

snmpTrapCommunity.name: snmpTrapCommunity
snmpTrapCommunity.description: The community name of the trap. Max. string length is 128 octets.

defaultSntpServer.name: defaultSntpServer
defaultSntpServer.description: The name of the SNTP server to be use by the system, unless overridden by a BOOTP or DHCP server. Max. string length is 128 octets.

sntpServer.name: sntpServer
sntpServer.description: The name of the SNTP server currently in use by the system. Max. string length is 128 octets.

awcFtMcastAddr.name: awcFtMcastAddr
awcFtMcastAddr.description: Count of multicast addresses observed by the system.

awcFtDsHost.name: awcFtDsHost
awcFtDsHost.description: Count of DS (infrastructure) host addresses observed by the system over its own DS network interface (Ethernet).

awcFtBridgeHost.name: awcFtBridgeHost
awcFtBridgeHost.description: Count of DS (infrastructure) host addresses observed by the system on the remote side of a bridge.

awcFtClientSTA.name: awcFtClientSTA
awcFtClientSTA.description: Count of Client Station addresses observed by the system.

awcFtClientSTASelf.name: awcFtClientSTASelf
awcFtClientSTASelf.description: Count of Client Stations which are Associated to the system.

awcFtBridge.name: awcFtBridge
awcFtBridge.description: Count of non-root Bridge addresses observed by the system.

awcFtBridgeSelf.name: awcFtBridgeSelf
awcFtBridgeSelf.description: Count of non-root Bridges which are Associated to the system.

awcFtRepeater.name: awcFtRepeater
awcFtRepeater.description: Count of Repeater addresses observed by the system.

awcFtRepeaterSelf.name: awcFtRepeaterSelf
awcFtRepeaterSelf.description: Count of Repeater devices which are Associated to the system.

awcFtAccessPoint.name: awcFtAccessPoint
awcFtAccessPoint.description: Count of Access Point addresses observed by the system.

awcFtBridgeRoot.name: awcFtBridgeRoot
awcFtBridgeRoot.description: Count of Root Bridge addresses observed by the system.

awcFtMaxNumEntries.name: awcFtMaxNumEntries
awcFtMaxNumEntries.description: The maximum number of entries in the forwarding table. Must be a power of 2 from 1024 to 65536. The number of entries controls the size of the forwarding table and the hash algorithm used by the forwarding table. Changing the number of entries requires a system reboot.

awcFtTimeoutSecUnknown.name: awcFtTimeoutSecUnknown
awcFtTimeoutSecUnknown.description: The default number of seconds an Entry with awcTpFdbClassID=unknown will remain in the Forwarding Table before being staled-out.

awcFtTimeoutSecMcastAddr.name: awcFtTimeoutSecMcastAddr
awcFtTimeoutSecMcastAddr.description: The default number of seconds an Entry with awcTpFdbClassID=multicast will remain in the Forwarding Table before being staled-out.

awcFtTimeoutSecDsHost.name: awcFtTimeoutSecDsHost
awcFtTimeoutSecDsHost.description: The default number of seconds an Entry with awcTpFdbClassID=dsHost will remain in the Forwarding Table before being staled-out.

awcFtTimeoutSecBridgeHost.name: awcFtTimeoutSecBridgeHost
awcFtTimeoutSecBridgeHost.description: The default number of seconds an Entry with awcTpFdbClassID=bridgeHost will remain in the Forwarding Table before being staled-out.

awcFtTimeoutSecClientSTA.name: awcFtTimeoutSecClientSTA
awcFtTimeoutSecClientSTA.description: The default number of seconds an Entry with awcTpFdbClassID=clientStation will remain in the Forwarding Table before being staled-out.

awcFtTimeoutSecBridge.name: awcFtTimeoutSecBridge
awcFtTimeoutSecBridge.description: The default number of seconds an Entry with awcTpFdbClassID=bridge will remain in the Forwarding Table before being staled-out.

awcFtTimeoutSecRepeater.name: awcFtTimeoutSecRepeater
awcFtTimeoutSecRepeater.description: The default number of seconds an Entry with awcTpFdbClassID=repeater will remain in the Forwarding Table before being staled-out.

awcFtTimeoutSecAccessPoint.name: awcFtTimeoutSecAccessPoint
awcFtTimeoutSecAccessPoint.description: The default number of seconds an Entry with awcTpFdbClassID=accessPoint will remain in the Forwarding Table before being staled-out.

awcFtTimeoutSecBridgeRoot.name: awcFtTimeoutSecBridgeRoot
awcFtTimeoutSecBridgeRoot.description: The default number of seconds an Entry with awcTpFdbClassID=bridgeRoot will remain in the Forwarding Table before being staled-out.

awcFtEnableAwcTpFdbTable.name: awcFtEnableAwcTpFdbTable
awcFtEnableAwcTpFdbTable.description: If true, the system will populate the awcTpFdbEntry MIB for all forwarding table entries. This improves management statistics. If false, the system will not populate the awcTpFdbEntry MIB for any forwarding table entries. This improves speed and memory utilization.

awcFtEnableMacAuthServer.name: awcFtEnableMacAuthServer
awcFtEnableMacAuthServer.description: If true, the system will contact a AAA server for retrieving dot1dStaticTable information for new forwarding table entries if a dot1dStaticTable entry does not already exist for the host address.

awcFtRogueApAlertTimeout.name: awcFtRogueApAlertTimeout
awcFtRogueApAlertTimeout.description: The minimum number of minutes after a Possible Rogue status is reported about a device before another Possible Rogue status report is issued by this system about the same device.

awcFtEnableMacOrEapAuth.name: awcFtEnableMacOrEapAuth
awcFtEnableMacOrEapAuth.description: If true, the system grants full access to those clients which have successfully completed either MAC or EAP authentication.

awcFtDot1dTpFdbTableEnable.name: awcFtDot1dTpFdbTableEnable
awcFtDot1dTpFdbTableEnable.description: If true, the system will populate the dot1dTpFdbEntry MIB for all forwarding table entries. This improves management statistics. If false, the system will not populate the dot1dTpFdbEntry MIB for any forwarding table entries. This improves speed and memory utilization.

awcTpFdbTable.name: awcTpFdbTable
awcTpFdbTable.description: A table that contains information about entries for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the transparent bridging function for maintaining statistics about each entry.

awcTpFdbEntry.name: awcTpFdbEntry
awcTpFdbEntry.description: Information about a specific MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

awcTpFdbAddress.name: awcTpFdbAddress
awcTpFdbAddress.description: A MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

awcTpFdbClassID.name: awcTpFdbClassID
awcTpFdbClassID.description: Observed general 802.11 classification of the entry.

awcTpFdbSrcPktsImmed.name: awcTpFdbSrcPktsImmed
awcTpFdbSrcPktsImmed.description: Number of observed packets for which this entry was the source.

awcTpFdbSrcOctetsImmed.name: awcTpFdbSrcOctetsImmed
awcTpFdbSrcOctetsImmed.description: Number of observed octets for which this entry was the source.

awcTpFdbSrcErrorPktsImmed.name: awcTpFdbSrcErrorPktsImmed
awcTpFdbSrcErrorPktsImmed.description: Number of observed error packets for which this entry was the source.

awcTpFdbSrcErrorOctetsImmed.name: awcTpFdbSrcErrorOctetsImmed
awcTpFdbSrcErrorOctetsImmed.description: Number of observed error octets for which this entry was the source.

awcTpFdbDestPktsImmed.name: awcTpFdbDestPktsImmed
awcTpFdbDestPktsImmed.description: Number of observed packets for which this entry was the destination.

awcTpFdbDestOctetsImmed.name: awcTpFdbDestOctetsImmed
awcTpFdbDestOctetsImmed.description: Number of observed octets for which this entry was the destination.

awcTpFdbDestErrorPktsImmed.name: awcTpFdbDestErrorPktsImmed
awcTpFdbDestErrorPktsImmed.description: Number of observed error packets for which this entry was the destination. This count includes awcTpFdbDestMaxRetryErrorsImmed.

awcTpFdbDestErrorOctetsImmed.name: awcTpFdbDestErrorOctetsImmed
awcTpFdbDestErrorOctetsImmed.description: Number of observed error octets for which this entry was the destination.

awcTpFdbDestMaxRetryErrorsImmed.name: awcTpFdbDestMaxRetryErrorsImmed
awcTpFdbDestMaxRetryErrorsImmed.description: Number of observed max-retry error packets for which this entry was the destination.

awcTpFdbIPv4Addr.name: awcTpFdbIPv4Addr
awcTpFdbIPv4Addr.description: Observed IPv4 network address of the entry.

awcTpFdbDdpTable.name: awcTpFdbDdpTable
awcTpFdbDdpTable.description: A table that contains information about entries for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information. This table maintains only Aironet-specific information about each entry.

awcTpFdbDdpEntry.name: awcTpFdbDdpEntry
awcTpFdbDdpEntry.description: Information about a specific MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

awcTpFdbDdpAddress.name: awcTpFdbDdpAddress
awcTpFdbDdpAddress.description: A MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

awcTpFdbDdpSysName.name: awcTpFdbDdpSysName
awcTpFdbDdpSysName.description: The Aironet DDP System Name of the entry.

awcTpFdbDdpProdDevID.name: awcTpFdbDdpProdDevID
awcTpFdbDdpProdDevID.description: The Aironet DDP Product Device ID of the entry.

awcTpFdbDdpRadioDevID.name: awcTpFdbDdpRadioDevID
awcTpFdbDdpRadioDevID.description: The Aironet DDP Radio Device ID of the entry.

awcTpFdbDdpSwVerMajor.name: awcTpFdbDdpSwVerMajor
awcTpFdbDdpSwVerMajor.description: The Aironet DDP Major Software Version Number of the entry. If unknown, the value 0 is returned.

awcTpFdbDdpSwVerMinor.name: awcTpFdbDdpSwVerMinor
awcTpFdbDdpSwVerMinor.description: The Aironet DDP Minor Software Version Number of the entry.

awcTpFdbDdpSwVerBeta.name: awcTpFdbDdpSwVerBeta
awcTpFdbDdpSwVerBeta.description: The Aironet DDP Beta Software Version Number of the entry. This number is always 0 for officially-released software.

awcTpFdbDdpUptime.name: awcTpFdbDdpUptime
awcTpFdbDdpUptime.description: The time in seconds that the entry has been operational.

awcTpFdbDdpNumAnnounceSent.name: awcTpFdbDdpNumAnnounceSent
awcTpFdbDdpNumAnnounceSent.description: The number of times the entry itself believes that it has issued some form of Aironet DDP Presense Announcement. If this field decreases, the entry has probably been reset.

awcTpFdbDdpNumAssociated.name: awcTpFdbDdpNumAssociated
awcTpFdbDdpNumAssociated.description: The number of Stations currently Associated with the entry.

awcTpFdbDdpLoad.name: awcTpFdbDdpLoad
awcTpFdbDdpLoad.description: An approximation of the percentage of offered vs. theoretically-available load on the host's radio interface.

awcTpFdbDdpDistFromDS.name: awcTpFdbDdpDistFromDS
awcTpFdbDdpDistFromDS.description: The Bridging Distance or Number of Hops between the entry and the backbone Distribution System (DS). If 0, the entry is directly connected to the DS.

awcDot11TpFdbTable.name: awcDot11TpFdbTable
awcDot11TpFdbTable.description: A table that contains information about entries for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information. This table maintains only 802.11-specific information about each entry.

awcDot11TpFdbEntry.name: awcDot11TpFdbEntry
awcDot11TpFdbEntry.description: Information about a specific MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

awcDot11TpFdbAddress.name: awcDot11TpFdbAddress
awcDot11TpFdbAddress.description: A MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

awcDot11TpFdbAID.name: awcDot11TpFdbAID
awcDot11TpFdbAID.description: AID with which the Station is associated with this system, or 2008 if the Station is not currently known to be associated. If the entry is multicast, awcDot11TpFdbAID is 0. Note that the uplink from a Client or Repeater AP to its parent is always AID 1.

awcDot11TpFdbTxShortRetries.name: awcDot11TpFdbTxShortRetries
awcDot11TpFdbTxShortRetries.description: The total number of 802.11 Short Retries incurred across all packet Transmission Attempts to this Station.

awcDot11TpFdbTxLongRetries.name: awcDot11TpFdbTxLongRetries
awcDot11TpFdbTxLongRetries.description: The total number of 802.11 Long Retries incurred across all packet Transmission Attempts to this Station.

awcDot11TpFdbLatestTxShortRetries.name: awcDot11TpFdbLatestTxShortRetries
awcDot11TpFdbLatestTxShortRetries.description: The number of 802.11 Short Retries incurred during the most recent packet Transmission Attempts to this Station.

awcDot11TpFdbLatestTxLongRetries.name: awcDot11TpFdbLatestTxLongRetries
awcDot11TpFdbLatestTxLongRetries.description: The number of 802.11 Long Retries incurred during the most recent packet Transmission Attempts to this Station.

awcDot11TpFdbRxWEPErrors.name: awcDot11TpFdbRxWEPErrors
awcDot11TpFdbRxWEPErrors.description: The total number of packets received from this Station which failed to be properly decrypted via the WEP security mechanism.

awcDot11TpFdbLatestRxSignalStrength.name: awcDot11TpFdbLatestRxSignalStrength
awcDot11TpFdbLatestRxSignalStrength.description: A device-dependent measure of the signal strength of the most recently received packet from this Station. Might be normalized or unnormalized.

awcDot11TpFdbLatestRxSignalQuality.name: awcDot11TpFdbLatestRxSignalQuality
awcDot11TpFdbLatestRxSignalQuality.description: A device-dependent measure of the signal quality of the most recently received packet from this Station.

awcDot11TpFdbCapabilities.name: awcDot11TpFdbCapabilities
awcDot11TpFdbCapabilities.description: The possible 802.11 capabilities of the Station's radio.

awcDot11TpFdbListenInterval.name: awcDot11TpFdbListenInterval
awcDot11TpFdbListenInterval.description: The number of beacon intervals across which a the Station will sleep in power-save mode, or 1 if the Station will never be in power-save mode.

awcDot11TpFdbSupportedDataRates.name: awcDot11TpFdbSupportedDataRates
awcDot11TpFdbSupportedDataRates.description: This attribute shall specify the set of data rates at which the station may transmit data. Each octet contains a value representing a rate. Each rate shall be within the range from 2 to 255, the lower seven bits 0..6 of which corresponding to data rates in increments of 500 kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s, and shall be supported (as indicated in the supported rates table) for receiving data. This value is reported in transmitted Beacon, Probe Request, Probe Response, Association Request, Association Response, Reassociation Request, and Reassociation Response frames, and is used to determine whether a BSS with which the station desires to synchronize is suitable. If set, Bit 7 of the rate specification indicates that rate is a member of the Basic Rate Set of the access point.

awcDot11TpFdbPreferredTxRate.name: awcDot11TpFdbPreferredTxRate
